==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Harebell
<hw>Hare"bell`</hw> <pr>(h⟦acir⟧r"b⟦ecr⟧l`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A small, slender, branching plant (<spn>Campanula
rotundifolia</spn>), having blue bell-shaped flowers; also, <spn>Scilla
nutans</spn>, which has similar flowers; -- called also
<altname>bluebell</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>hairbell</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>E'en the light <qex>harebell</qex> raised its head.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 671 pr=JMD --></p>

<p><ent>Harebrained</ent>⟦br⟧
